---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>My Second Country · A second country, decided on evidence.</title>
<meta name="description" content="My Second Country screens countries, regions, and towns using cited relocation facts, verified dates, and confidence marks.">
<link rel="canonical" href="https://mysecondcountry.com/">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Newsreader:ital,opsz,wght@0,6..72,400;0,6..72,500;0,6..72,600;0,6..72,700;1,6..72,400&family=Inter:wght@400;500;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/brand/favicon.svg">
<script defer data-domain="mysecondcountry.com" src="https://plausible.io/js/script.outbound-links.tagged-events.js"></script>
<script>
  window.plausible =
    window.plausible ||
    function () {
      (window.plausible.q = window.plausible.q || []).push(arguments);
    };
</script>

<script type="application/ld+json">
[
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebSite",
    "name": "My Second Country",
    "url": "https://mysecondcountry.com/",
    "description": "Cited relocation intelligence: every cost, tax, visa, residency, climate, healthcare, and safety figure is a sourced, dated claim with a confidence mark that links to its primary source."
  },
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is this advice?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "No. We screen published rules and show you sourced figures. We are not lawyers or tax advisers; for the decision itself we point you to professionals."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which countries can I compare?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "A growing set. We add a country only once its data clears the same sourcing bar. You can see the ones covered today on the compare page."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How current is the data?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Every figure shows the date we last verified it and how confident we are. Rule-based figures like tax and visa rules are rechecked more often than slow-moving ones like climate."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What does it cost?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Building a shortlist is free. We may earn a fee only if you choose an introduction we suggest, and we disclose it before you decide. Nothing pays for placement."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How is this different from the usual sites?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "They give you a number. We give you the number plus its source, its date, and our confidence in it, so you can check us rather than take our word."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
]
</script>

<!-- SHARED FOUNDATION + SECTION LIBRARY -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/mockups/_msc-system.css">

<style is:global>
/* ============================================================
   FULL HOMEPAGE — assembled from the locked section mockups
   (gates 12-17) + the shared CTA band. Section CSS concatenated
   below; each section keeps its own prefixed classes. Band rhythm
   alternates paper / paper-warm down the page.
   ============================================================ */
/* ===== gate-12-hero.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 12 — HOMEPAGE HERO (full-bleed engraving + LIVE shortlist)
   The engraving (Chania harbour) bleeds full-width and dissolves
   into the page via multiply (the footer device): background layer +
   soft paper veil over the top so the copy stays crisp. The promise
   sits over the open water on the left; on the right, a real product
   glimpse: a working "Your shortlist" demo driven by the locked
   scenario chips (gate 11). Choosing a situation re-ranks the three
   places with the relevant cited figure each (real source/date/
   confidence, citation on tap). All figures from packages/data/src.
   On lock -> generalise the footer scene into a shared `.eng-band`.
   ============================================================ */
.hero-band {
  position: relative;
  isolation: isolate;
  background-color: var(--paper);
  background-image:
    linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--paper) 8%, rgba(252,252,252,0.5) 38%, rgba(252,252,252,0.08) 66%, rgba(252,252,252,0) 84%),
    url("/mockups/img/engravings/hero.png");
  background-repeat: no-repeat, no-repeat;
  background-position: center, center 42%;
  background-size: 100% 100%, cover;
  background-blend-mode: normal, multiply;
  min-height: clamp(580px, 64vw, 860px);
  padding: clamp(40px, 6vw, 84px) 0 clamp(40px, 6vw, 76px);
}

.hero-band__inner {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  column-gap: clamp(28px, 5vw, 80px);
  align-items: center;
  min-height: clamp(440px, 48vw, 660px);
}

.hero-copy { max-width: 34rem; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 26px; }
.hero-actions { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 20px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.hero-fence { max-width: 34rem; }
.hero-fence .fence { margin: 0; }

/* ---- the live shortlist artifact (LOCKED size, premium) ----
   Fixed width; every scenario renders to the same height because the
   chips, the ranked-by caption, and three uniform rows are constant.
   Row meta is single-line (ellipsis) so switching options never reflows.
   Citations reset closed on each render, so size is stable across
   options; a citation a user opens expands below, identically each time. */
.ls {
  justify-self: end;
  width: min(100%, 452px);
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft);
  border-radius: 22px;
  padding: clamp(22px, 2vw, 28px);
  box-shadow: 0 14px 50px rgba(26,24,19,0.14), 0 2px 8px rgba(26,24,19,0.05);
}

.ls__head { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; padding-bottom: 16px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.ls__label { margin: 0; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); font-weight: 400; color: var(--ink-soft); letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase; }
.ls__for { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); }
.ls__for strong { color: var(--pop-ink); font-weight: 700; }

.ls__chips { margin-top: 16px; gap: 8px; }
.ls__chips .chip { font-size: 0.8rem; padding: 9px 14px; }
/* min-height inherits the system .chip 44px floor (touch target) */

.ls__rankedby { margin-top: 16px; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); letter-spacing: 0.02em; }

.ls__list { list-style: none; margin: 8px 0 0; padding: 0; }
/* rows are persistent elements reordered with a FLIP animation on
   scenario change (handled in JS); height stays constant. */
.ls__row {
  position: relative;
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 24px minmax(0, 1fr) auto;
  column-gap: 14px;
  align-items: center;
  padding: 13px 12px;
  margin: 3px -12px 0;
  border-radius: 14px;
  transition: background 200ms var(--ease);
}
.ls__row:hover { background: var(--paper-warm); }
/* rank-1 carries no winner styling: the rank numeral conveys sort order
   only (no endorsement), per the no-recommendation doctrine. */

.ls__rank {
  grid-row: 1; align-self: center;
  width: 24px; height: 24px;
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--stone);
  border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); border-radius: 999px;
  transition: background 200ms var(--ease), color 200ms var(--ease), border-color 200ms var(--ease);
}

.ls__main { grid-row: 1; min-width: 0; }
.ls__placeline { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; min-width: 0; }
.ls__placename { font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-size: 1.08rem; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.2; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }
.ls__meta { display: block; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); margin-top: 4px; white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; }

.ls__right { grid-row: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-end; gap: 5px; text-align: right; }
.ls__val { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; white-space: nowrap; line-height: 1.05; }
.ls__unit { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); font-weight: 400; color: var(--stone); margin-left: 2px; }
.ls__prov { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; white-space: nowrap; }
.ls__conf { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); }
.ls__conf svg { flex-shrink: 0; }
.ls__sep { color: var(--hairline-soft); font-size: var(--t-meta); }

.cite.ls__cite { display: inline; position: relative; border: none; background: none; padding: 0; min-width: 0; min-height: 0; color: var(--stone); font-size: var(--t-meta); line-height: 1.4; }
/* transparent hit-area enlarges the inline Source toggle's tap target
   without changing the refined provenance row layout */
.cite.ls__cite::before { content: ""; position: absolute; inset: -10px -6px; }
.cite.ls__cite::after {
  content: ""; display: inline-block; width: 5px; height: 5px; margin-left: 5px; vertical-align: middle;
  border-right: 1.4px solid currentColor; border-bottom: 1.4px solid currentColor;
  transform: rotate(45deg) translateY(-1px); transition: transform 200ms var(--ease);
}
.cite.ls__cite[aria-expanded="true"]::after { transform: rotate(-135deg) translateY(1px); }
.cite.ls__cite:hover, .cite.ls__cite:focus-visible { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: underline; }

.ls__panel { grid-column: 1 / -1; grid-row: 2; }
.ls__panel.cite-panel-wrap.open { margin-top: 11px; }
.ls__panel .cite-panel { max-width: none; }

.ls__more { margin-top: 16px; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: var(--t-bodysm); }

/* phone: copy on paper at top, artifact below, engraving dissolving beneath */
@media (max-width: 860px) {
  .hero-band {
    min-height: 0;
    padding-bottom: clamp(200px, 52vw, 340px);
    background-size: 100% 100%, 150% auto;
    background-position: top center, bottom center;
  }
  .hero-band__inner { display: block; min-height: 0; }
  .hero-copy { max-width: none; margin-bottom: 30px; }
  .ls { justify-self: stretch; width: 100%; }
}

/* ===== gate-13-problem.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 13 — THE PROBLEM ("anatomy of a number")
   No cards, no illustration. The wow is a single real cited figure
   exploded into everything that stands behind it (source, verified
   date, confidence, basis, fence), connected by fine leader lines
   that draw in on scroll, like a precise scientific / data-journalism
   figure. The turn names the enemy: most numbers you find carry none
   of this. Type + real cited data only. On lock -> homepage build.
   ============================================================ */
.problem { background: var(--paper-warm); padding: clamp(72px, 10vw, 144px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); overflow: hidden; }

.problem-head { max-width: 64ch; }
.problem-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 20ch; }
.problem-lead { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: clamp(var(--t-lead), 1.5vw, 1.2rem); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.58; max-width: 54ch; margin-top: 18px; }

/* ---- the anatomy diagram ---- */
.anatomy {
  margin-top: clamp(52px, 7vw, 96px);
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: auto clamp(30px, 5vw, 76px) minmax(0, 1fr);
  align-items: center;
}

.anatomy__fig { text-align: right; padding-right: 2px; }
.anatomy__figlabel { display: block; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone); margin-bottom: 12px; }
.anatomy__num { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-weight: 500; font-size: clamp(5.25rem, 15vw, 11.5rem); line-height: 0.8; color: var(--ink); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; letter-spacing: -0.035em; display: inline-block; }
.anatomy__unit { font-size: 0.32em; color: var(--stone); margin-left: 0.06em; letter-spacing: 0; }

.anatomy__stem { height: 1.5px; background: var(--accent); align-self: center; }

.anatomy__rows { border-left: 1.5px solid var(--accent); margin: 0; }
.anatomy__row { position: relative; display: grid; grid-template-columns: 8em minmax(0, 1fr); align-items: baseline; gap: 4px 16px; padding: clamp(13px, 1.5vw, 19px) 0 clamp(13px, 1.5vw, 19px) clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 36px); }
.anatomy__row + .anatomy__row { border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
/* the leader tick that connects the bracket to each row, drawn on reveal */
.anatomy__row::before { content: ""; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 50%; height: 1.5px; width: clamp(16px, 2.2vw, 30px); background: var(--accent); transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(0); transform-origin: left center; transition: transform 520ms var(--ease); }
.anatomy__row.in::before { transform: translateY(-50%) scaleX(1); }
.anatomy__k { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); letter-spacing: 0.08em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone); }
.anatomy__v { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-body); color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.45; }
.anatomy__v--quote { margin: 0; font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.4; }
.anatomy__conf { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-bodysm); color: var(--ink-soft); }
.anatomy__conf svg { flex-shrink: 0; }
.anatomy__link { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
.anatomy__link:hover, .anatomy__link:focus-visible { text-decoration: underline; }
.anatomy__link svg { margin-left: 4px; vertical-align: -1px; }

.problem-kicker { margin-top: clamp(30px, 4vw, 48px); font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(1.4rem, 2.6vw, 2.1rem); line-height: 1.34; letter-spacing: -0.016em; color: var(--ink-soft); max-width: 32ch; }
.problem-kicker b { font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; color: var(--pop-ink); }

@media (max-width: 760px) {
  .anatomy { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .anatomy__fig { text-align: left; padding-right: 0; }
  .anatomy__stem { display: none; }
  .anatomy__rows { margin-top: 28px; }
  .anatomy__row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 3px; }
  .anatomy__k { margin-bottom: 1px; }
}

/* ===== gate-14-howitworks.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 14 — HOW IT WORKS (type + evidence led, three steps)
   No stock icons, no illustration. Big mono step numerals on a
   broadsheet baseline rule, Newsreader titles, tight copy, and each
   step grounded in a REAL artifact: the actual input chips, the real
   source families we cite, and a real cited result. Input -> sources
   -> output, shown with evidence. On lock -> homepage build.
   ============================================================ */
.howit { background: var(--paper); padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 140px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }

.howit-head { max-width: 62ch; }
.howit-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 22ch; }
.howit-lead { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: clamp(var(--t-lead), 1.5vw, 1.2rem); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.58; max-width: 56ch; margin-top: 18px; }

.howit-steps { margin-top: clamp(46px, 6vw, 84px); display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); border-top: 1.5px solid var(--ink); }
@media (max-width: 760px) { .howit-steps { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

.step { display: flex; flex-direction: column; padding: clamp(26px, 2.6vw, 38px) clamp(22px, 2.2vw, 34px) clamp(8px, 1vw, 14px); }
.step:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
.step:last-child { padding-right: 0; }
.step + .step { border-left: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
@media (max-width: 760px) {
  .step { padding: clamp(28px, 6vw, 40px) 0 clamp(20px, 4vw, 28px); }
  .step + .step { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
}

.step__num { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: clamp(2rem, 3.4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); letter-spacing: -0.02em; line-height: 1; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.step__title { font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-weight: 400; font-size: var(--t-sub); line-height: 1.18; letter-spacing: -0.018em; color: var(--ink); margin: 16px 0 0; }
.step__body { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-bodysm); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.6; margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 34ch; }

.step__art { margin-top: auto; padding-top: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 30px); }
.step__artlabel { display: block; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: 0.68rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone); margin-bottom: 12px; }

/* step 1 — input chips (static glimpse of the scenario picker) */
.step-chips { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
.step-chip { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-meta); font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); background: var(--surface); border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); border-radius: 999px; padding: 7px 13px; }
.step-chip.is-on { background: var(--accent); border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--paper); }

/* step 2 — the real source families */
.step-sources { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; }
.step-src { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); border-radius: 6px; padding: 5px 9px; }

/* step 3 — a real cited result (open, ledger style, no card) */
.step-result__row { display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 12px; }
.step-result__place { font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-size: 1.05rem; color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.2; }
.step-result__val { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: 1.0625rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); white-space: nowrap; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
.step-result__unit { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); font-weight: 400; color: var(--stone); margin-left: 4px; }
.step-result__prov { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 9px; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); }
.step-result__conf { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; }
.step-result__conf svg { flex-shrink: 0; }
.step-result__sep { color: var(--hairline-soft); }

/* ===== gate-18-bento.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 18 — HOW TO READ IT (bento)
   A gapless tile grid that teaches the SYSTEM (not shown as a
   standalone anywhere else): the confidence marks, the dimensions
   every country gets, and the source/date/confidence triad. Breaks
   the middle type-run with a real visual grid. One
   bordered grid with shared hairlines, never floating cards. On a
   stone band so it reads as a third tone between paper and warm.
   On lock -> homepage build (placed after "how it works").
   ============================================================ */
.bento-band { background: var(--paper-stone); padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 140px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.bento-head { max-width: 44ch; }
.bento-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 20ch; }
.bento-lead { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: clamp(var(--t-lead), 1.5vw, 1.2rem); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.58; max-width: 52ch; margin-top: 16px; }

.bento {
  margin-top: clamp(40px, 5vw, 64px);
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1.25fr 1fr;
  grid-template-areas:
    "conf dims"
    "conf triad";
  background: var(--surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft);
  border-radius: var(--radius-card);
  overflow: hidden;
}
.bento__tile { padding: clamp(22px, 2.5vw, 34px); }
.bento__tile--conf { grid-area: conf; border-right: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.bento__tile--dims { grid-area: dims; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.bento__tile--triad { grid-area: triad; }

@media (max-width: 720px) {
  .bento { grid-template-columns: 1fr; grid-template-areas: "conf" "dims" "triad"; }
  .bento__tile--conf { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
  .bento__tile--triad { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
}

.bento__label { display: block; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone); }
.bento__h { font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1.35rem; line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.014em; color: var(--ink); margin: 8px 0 0; }

.bento__conf { list-style: none; margin: 18px 0 0; padding: 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 16px; }
.bento__conf li { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 7.5em 1fr; gap: 4px 14px; align-items: baseline; }
@media (max-width: 460px) { .bento__conf li { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2px; } }
.bento__mk { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-bodysm); color: var(--ink); white-space: nowrap; }
.bento__mk svg { flex-shrink: 0; }
.bento__gl { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-bodysm); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.5; }

.bento__dims { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 8px; margin-top: 18px; }
.bento__dim { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--ink-soft); border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); border-radius: 999px; padding: 5px 12px; }

.bento__triad { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-body); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.6; margin-top: 16px; max-width: 34ch; }
.bento__triad b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }

/* ===== gate-15-coverage.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 15 — WHERE IT RUNS DEEPEST (coverage + compare glimpse)
   Merges the old "see a real result" + "coverage": honest scope
   (Greece, Portugal, Spain deep today; global ambition) PROVEN with a
   real cited side-by-side comparison, the depth/decision the hero's
   shortlist never shows. Reuses the locked comparison-table component
   (gate 8) in a lighter homepage glimpse (source named, no expandable
   panel; full cited version on the compare page). Figures vary from
   earlier sections (cost / tax / sunshine / safety, not 7% again).
   On lock -> homepage build.
   ============================================================ */
.coverage { background: var(--paper-warm); padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 140px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }

.coverage-head { max-width: 64ch; }
.coverage-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 18ch; }
.coverage-lead { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: clamp(var(--t-lead), 1.5vw, 1.2rem); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.58; max-width: 60ch; margin-top: 18px; }

/* homepage glimpse: the shared comparison table, not sticky here, lighter cells */
.coverage-sample { margin-top: clamp(40px, 5vw, 64px); font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone); }
.coverage .ctable { margin-top: 14px; max-width: none; }
.coverage .ctable-head { position: static; }
.cov-src { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); }

.coverage-foot { margin-top: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px); display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.coverage-note { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 56ch; }
.coverage-link { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-body); font-weight: 700; color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 7px; white-space: nowrap; }
.coverage-link:hover, .coverage-link:focus-visible { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ===== evidence dossier shelf ===== */
.dossier-shelf { background: var(--paper); padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 132px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.dossier-head { display: grid; grid-template-columns: minmax(16rem, 0.72fr) minmax(0, 1fr); gap: clamp(24px, 5vw, 84px); align-items: end; }
.dossier-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 14ch; }
.dossier-lead { margin: 0; max-width: 56ch; font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-body); line-height: 1.62; color: var(--ink-soft); }
.dossier-grid { margin-top: clamp(38px, 5vw, 64px); display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 1px; background: var(--hairline-soft); border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.dossier-file { display: flex; min-height: 232px; flex-direction: column; justify-content: space-between; gap: 28px; padding: clamp(22px, 2.8vw, 34px); background: var(--paper); color: var(--ink); text-decoration: none; }
.dossier-file:hover, .dossier-file:focus-visible { background: var(--paper-warm); color: var(--ink); }
.dossier-file:focus-visible { outline: 2px solid var(--accent); outline-offset: -2px; }
.dossier-file__meta { font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); color: var(--stone); text-transform: uppercase; }
.dossier-file__title { margin: 0; font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-weight: 400; font-size: 1.55rem; line-height: 1.14; color: var(--ink); }
.dossier-file__copy { margin: 12px 0 0; font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-bodysm); line-height: 1.55; color: var(--ink-soft); }
.dossier-foot { margin-top: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px); display: flex; align-items: baseline; justify-content: space-between; gap: 16px 28px; flex-wrap: wrap; }
.dossier-note { margin: 0; max-width: 58ch; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); line-height: 1.6; color: var(--stone); }
@media (max-width: 900px) {
  .dossier-head { grid-template-columns: 1fr; align-items: start; }
  .dossier-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr)); }
}
@media (max-width: 620px) {
  .dossier-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  .dossier-file { min-height: 188px; }
}

/* ===== gate-16-who.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 16 — WHO MAKES THIS (the people + the integrity stance)
   Type-led, evergreen (no country names, no figures). A founders'
   note in the Newsreader italic analyst voice carries the human/why;
   a tight hairline list of integrity promises carries the trust we
   pulled out of the cut "why trust it" pillars, including the honest-
   money stance (screening not advice, nothing buys a ranking, fees
   disclosed). On lock -> homepage build.
   ============================================================ */
.who { background: var(--paper); padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 140px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }

.who-inner { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.05fr 0.95fr; gap: clamp(40px, 6vw, 92px); align-items: start; }
@media (max-width: 860px) { .who-inner { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: clamp(40px, 8vw, 56px); } }

.who-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; max-width: 18ch; }
.who-note { margin-top: clamp(26px, 3vw, 38px); }
.who-note p { margin-top: 0.6em; }
.who-note p:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
.who-sign { margin-top: clamp(22px, 2.4vw, 30px); font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); letter-spacing: 0.04em; color: var(--stone); }

.who-right { padding-top: clamp(6px, 1vw, 14px); }
.who-right__label { display: block; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: var(--t-meta); letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--stone); margin-bottom: 4px; }

.integrity { list-style: none; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
.integrity__item { padding: clamp(18px, 2vw, 24px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
.integrity__item:first-child { border-top: 1.5px solid var(--ink); }
.integrity__item:last-child { padding-bottom: 0; }
.integrity__lead { font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.8vw, 1.5rem); line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: -0.014em; color: var(--ink); display: flex; align-items: baseline; gap: 12px; }
.integrity__lead::before { content: ""; flex: 0 0 auto; width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 999px; background: var(--pop); transform: translateY(-0.18em); }
.integrity__gloss { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-bodysm); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.6; margin: 9px 0 0 19px; max-width: 48ch; }

/* ===== gate-17-faq.html ===== */
/* ============================================================
   GATE 17 — QUESTIONS ANSWERED (compact FAQ, broadsheet Q|A)
   Type-led, evergreen, no cards. A definition-list layout: question
   left, answer right, hairline-divided, like a glossary. Handles the
   objections (advice, cost, currency, difference) and the coverage
   question NEUTRALLY (points to the live, data-driven list rather
   than naming a roster). On lock -> homepage build; the homepage then
   closes with the shared CTA band (gate 6) + footer.
   ============================================================ */
.faq { background: var(--paper-warm); padding: clamp(72px, 9vw, 140px) 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }

.faq-head { max-width: 30ch; }
.faq-head .display-section { margin: 10px 0 0; }

.faq-list { margin-top: clamp(40px, 5vw, 68px); border-top: 1.5px solid var(--ink); }
.faq-item { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 0.85fr 1.15fr; gap: clamp(12px, 3vw, 56px); align-items: start; padding: clamp(22px, 2.6vw, 32px) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft); }
@media (max-width: 720px) { .faq-item { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 10px; padding: clamp(22px, 6vw, 28px) 0; } }

.faq-q { font-family: var(--f-display); font-optical-sizing: auto; font-weight: 400; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 1.9vw, 1.6rem); line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: -0.016em; color: var(--ink); }
.faq-a { font-family: var(--f-ui); font-size: var(--t-body); color: var(--ink-soft); line-height: 1.62; max-width: 56ch; }
.faq-a a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
.faq-a a:hover, .faq-a a:focus-visible { text-decoration: underline; }

/* ===== homepage overrides ===== */
/* Closing CTA — imageless, type-led.
   Place imagery on this page lives in the hero, the mid-page engraving
   moments, and the footer. The closing invitation is an ACTION surface,
   so per the locked register split it stays type-and-evidence-led: a
   quiet warm broadsheet card, framed by a fine inset rule for craft, the
   wow from type and scale rather than a scene. */
.cta-card {
  background-color: var(--paper-warm);
  background-image: none;
}
.cta-card::before {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: clamp(13px, 1.5vw, 20px);
  border: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft);
  border-radius: calc(var(--radius-card) - 14px);
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: 0;
}
.cta-card > * { position: relative; z-index: 1; }
.cta-eyebrow { margin-bottom: 0; }
@media (max-width: 520px) {
  .cta-card { background-image: none; }
  .cta-card::before { inset: 11px; }
}

/* ===== mid-page engraving band (evergreen "anywhere") =====
   Full-bleed engraving on a pure-paper ground (multiply drops the white),
   a soft paper veil keeps the centred line legible. The site's signature
   image device, reused once mid-page; a different global location from the
   hero (Amalfi), the Alps block above, and the footer (Greek coast). */
.place-band {
  position: relative;
  isolation: isolate;
  overflow: hidden;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--hairline-soft);
  background-color: var(--paper);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  min-height: clamp(360px, 44vw, 560px);
}
/* engraving on its own oversized layer so the subtle parallax never exposes
   an edge; background-blend multiply drops its white ground onto the paper. */
.place-band__bg {
  position: absolute;
  inset: -72px 0;
  z-index: 0;
  background-color: var(--paper);
  background-image: url("/mockups/img/engravings/benefit-3.png"); /* benefit-3.png = Japan coastal village scene */
  background-position: center 34%;
  background-size: cover;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-blend-mode: multiply;
}
/* soft paper veil keeps the centred line legible (sits above the engraving,
   below the copy, and does not move with the parallax). */
.place-band::after {
  content: "";
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 1;
  pointer-events: none;
  background: radial-gradient(58% 74% at 50% 52%, rgba(252,252,252,0.90) 0%, rgba(252,252,252,0.36) 46%, rgba(252,252,252,0) 78%);
}
.place-band .shell { position: relative; z-index: 2; }
.place-band-inner {
  max-width: 52ch;
  margin-inline: auto;
  text-align: center;
  padding-block: clamp(56px, 8vw, 112px);
}
.place-band-line {
  font-family: var(--f-display);
  font-weight: 500;
  font-size: clamp(1.85rem, 3.4vw, 2.9rem);
  line-height: 1.12;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  color: var(--ink);
  max-width: 18ch;
  margin: 0 auto 16px;
}
.place-band-sub {
  font-family: var(--f-ui);
  font-size: var(--t-body);
  line-height: 1.55;
  color: var(--ink-soft);
  max-width: 46ch;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
@media (max-width: 600px) {
  .place-band::after {
    background: radial-gradient(98% 88% at 50% 52%, rgba(252,252,252,0.94) 0%, rgba(252,252,252,0.82) 54%, rgba(252,252,252,0) 92%);
  }
}

/* the mid-page Alps place block sits on a warm band (class, not inline) */
.benefit--warm { background: var(--paper-warm); }

/* evergreen qualifier under the footer coverage list (not a fixed roster) */
.footer-cov-note { display: block; margin-top: 12px; font-family: var(--f-mono); font-size: 0.7rem; letter-spacing: 0.01em; color: var(--stone); }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>

<header class="site-header" role="banner">
  <div class="shell">
    <div class="site-header-inner">
      <a class="brand-wordmark" href="/" aria-label="My Second Country home">
        <img class="brand-icon" src="/brand/monogram.svg" alt="" width="36" height="36">
        <span class="brand-rule" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="brand-name">My Second Country</span>
      </a>
      <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Primary">
        {
          primaryNav.map((item) => (
            <a class="nav-link" href={item.href}>{item.label}</a>
          ))
        }
      </nav>
      <div class="nav-cta">
        <a href="/screener" class="btn-primary">Build my shortlist
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M2 12L12 2M12 2H5M12 2V9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </a>
      </div>
      <button class="nav-toggle" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="mobile-menu" aria-label="Open menu">
        <svg width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 20 20" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M3 6h14M3 10h14M3 14h14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round"/></svg>
      </button>
    </div>
    <div class="nav-menu" id="mobile-menu" hidden>
      {
        primaryNav.map((item) => (
          <a class="nav-link" href={item.href}>{item.label}</a>
        ))
      }
      <a href="/screener" class="btn-primary">Build my shortlist</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<main id="main-content">

<!-- ===== gate-12-hero.html ===== -->
<section class="hero-band" aria-labelledby="hero-heading">
  <div class="shell hero-band__inner">

    <!-- promise + action, over the open water -->
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <div class="hero-load" style="transition-delay:0ms;">
        <span class="overline">Cited relocation intelligence</span>
        <h1 id="hero-heading" class="display-hero">A second country,<br>decided on evidence.</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-fence hero-load" style="transition-delay:60ms;">
        <FenceBlock hasLegalClaims={true} />
      </div>
      <p class="standfirst hero-load" style="transition-delay:80ms;">
        Put your situation in. Get back a shortlist of countries, regions, and towns, each figure shown with its source, its verified date, and a confidence mark.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions hero-load" style="transition-delay:160ms;">
        <a href="/screener" class="btn-primary">
          Build my shortlist
          <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M2 12L12 2M12 2H5M12 2V9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/methodology" class="text-link">See the methodology</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- the live shortlist artifact (interactive) -->
    <aside class="ls hero-load" style="transition-delay:240ms;" aria-label="Sample shortlist, interactive">
      <div class="ls__head">
        <h2 class="ls__label">Your shortlist</h2>
        <span class="ls__for">for <strong id="ls-scenario-name">lower my taxes</strong></span>
      </div>

      <div class="chip-row ls__chips" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Your situation">
        <label class="chip"><input type="radio" name="ls-scenario" value="tax" autocomplete="off" checked> Lower my taxes</label>
        <label class="chip"><input type="radio" name="ls-scenario" value="remote" autocomplete="off"> Work remotely</label>
        <label class="chip"><input type="radio" name="ls-scenario" value="retire" autocomplete="off"> Retire abroad</label>
      </div>

      <p class="ls__rankedby" id="ls-rankedby" aria-live="polite"></p>
      <ol class="ls__list" id="ls-list" aria-live="polite"></ol>

      <a class="ls__more text-link" href="/compare/greece-portugal-spain">See the full comparison
        <svg width="13" height="13" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M2 12L12 2M12 2H5M12 2V9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg>
      </a>
    </aside>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== gate-13-problem.html ===== -->
<section class="problem" aria-labelledby="problem-heading">
  <div class="shell">

    <header class="problem-head" data-reveal style="--i:0">
      <span class="overline">The problem</span>
      <h2 id="problem-heading" class="display-section">Most relocation numbers can't be checked.</h2>
      <p class="problem-lead">A figure is only worth what stands behind it. Here is one of ours, in full.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="anatomy">
      <div class="anatomy__fig" data-reveal style="--i:0">
        <span class="anatomy__figlabel">Greece · foreign-pensioner flat tax</span>
        <span class="anatomy__num">7<span class="anatomy__unit">%</span></span>
      </div>

      <div class="anatomy__stem" data-reveal style="--i:0" aria-hidden="true"></div>

      <dl class="anatomy__rows" aria-label="Anatomy of one cited figure">
        <div class="anatomy__row" data-reveal style="--i:1">
          <dt class="anatomy__k">Source</dt>
          <dd class="anatomy__v"><a class="anatomy__link" href="https://taxsummaries.pwc.com/greece/individual/other-tax-credits-and-incentives" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">PwC Worldwide Tax Summaries, Greece<svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M2 12L12 2M12 2H5M12 2V9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy__row" data-reveal style="--i:2">
          <dt class="anatomy__k">Verified</dt>
          <dd class="anatomy__v"><span class="num" style="font-family:var(--f-mono)">2026-06-24</span></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy__row" data-reveal style="--i:3">
          <dt class="anatomy__k">Confidence</dt>
          <dd class="anatomy__v"><span class="anatomy__conf"><svg width="11" height="11" viewBox="0 0 10 10" aria-hidden="true"><rect x="0.5" y="0.5" width="9" height="9" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/><rect x="0.5" y="0.5" width="4.75" height="9" fill="currentColor"/></svg>medium</span></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy__row" data-reveal style="--i:4">
          <dt class="anatomy__k">Basis</dt>
          <dd class="anatomy__v">Article 5B, foreign-source pension income, up to 15 years</dd>
        </div>
        <div class="anatomy__row" data-reveal style="--i:5">
          <dt class="anatomy__k">Excerpt</dt>
          <dd class="anatomy__v"><blockquote class="anatomy__v--quote" cite="https://taxsummaries.pwc.com/greece/individual/other-tax-credits-and-incentives">"7 percent on foreign-sourced income (Art 5B), each for up to 15 fiscal years."</blockquote></dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <p class="problem-kicker" data-reveal style="--i:6">What you usually get is the number and nothing else: <b>undated, unsourced, and quietly sponsored.</b> We publish everything behind it.</p>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ===== gate-14-howitworks.html ===== -->
<section class="howit" aria-labelledby="howit-heading">
  <div class="shell">

    <header class="howit-head" data-reveal style="--i:0">
      <span class="overline">How it works</span>
      <h2 id="howit-heading" class="display-section">From your situation to a sourced shortlist.</h2>
      <p class="howit-lead">No account, no sales call. You answer a few questions, we screen your situation against published rules, and you get back a shortlist you can check yourself.</p>
    </header>

    <div class="howit-steps">

      <div class="step" data-reveal style="--i:0">
        <span class="step__num">01</span>
        <h3 class="step__title">Tell us your situation</h3>
        <p class="step__body">Household, citizenship, income, and what you want from a place. About two minutes, no account needed.</p>
        <div class="step__art">
          <span class="step__artlabel">You pick</span>
          <div class="step-chips">
            <span class="step-chip is-on">Lower my taxes</span>
            <span class="step-chip">Work remotely</span>
            <span class="step-chip">Retire abroad</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step" data-reveal style="--i:1">
        <span class="step__num">02</span>
        <h3 class="step__title">Screened against published rules</h3>
        <p class="step__body">We match it to visa, tax, cost, climate, healthcare, and safety data, every figure from a named public source.</p>
        <div class="step__art">
          <span class="step__artlabel">We cite</span>
          <div class="step-sources">
            <span class="step-src">Eurostat</span>
            <span class="step-src">PwC</span>
            <span class="step-src">Migration ministries</span>
            <span class="step-src">WHO</span>
            <span class="step-src">GPI</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step" data-reveal style="--i:2">
        <span class="step__num">03</span>
        <h3 class="step__title">A sourced shortlist</h3>
        <p class="step__body">Countries, regions, and towns sorted by the metric you chose, each figure shown with its source, date, and confidence.</p>
